         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Chief Secretary's Office ¶ Melbourne 21st December 1870 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I am directed by the Honorable the Chief Secretary to inform you, that you have been appointed by the Governor in Council the Chairma...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M70.12.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>William Odgers to William Hammill</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 3970, unit 23, pp. 654-5, VPRS 1187/P letters outwards October-December 1870, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office of Victoria, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Chief Secretary's Office</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne 21st December 1870</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am directed by the Honorable the Chief Secretary to inform you, that you have been appointed by the Governor in Council the Chairman of a Board consisting of the gentlemen named in the margin<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The names listed in the margin are W. Hammill, W. J. Greig, Josiah Mitchell and W. Sangster.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to inquire into and advise the Government upon the best mode of reorganizing the department of the Botanic Gardens.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The general direction which the Government desires the inquiry should<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>take will<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>apparent<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to the Board by a perusal of the enclosed extract from the minute laid before the Governor in Council on which the Order in Council was issued directing the appointment of the Board.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M was informed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the same day; W. Odgers to M, 21 December 1870 (in this edition as 70-12-21a).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="color: #0070C0; background-color: #FFFF00; ">The terms of reference, '"to inquire into and report on the Changes that may be necessary to bring into operation an organisation which will secure the Gardens being kept in the best possible condition, without in any way interfering with the valuable services rendered to the Colony by Dr von Mueller as a Botanist', are included in the report of the board., W. Greig and others to C. Gavan Duffy, 14 December 1871 (in this edition as M71.12.14.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; background-color: #FFFF00; ">This</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is really a holding<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">note<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">in case we can't find an original of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">O</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">rder. It would be better if we could get</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>i</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">t to include it h</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">er</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">e as an enclosure.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>It is supposed to be at<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>(<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">Minute 88, unit 12, pp. 352-3, VPRS 1080, Public Record Office, Victoria</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">).according to the note on 70-12-21a.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">Otherwise we can cross</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">-</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">refer to t</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">he notes on 70</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">-12-21a</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>But it is not intended that the Board should consider itself debarred from extending its investigation into any other branch of the subject that may come under view during the progress of the inquiry.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir James McCulloch requests that you will place yourself in communication with the other members of the Board and enter upon the inquiry at the earliest convenience of all concerned.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. H. Odgers</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">W. Hammill Esqre</p>
         </div>
      </body>
